Definitely the best dining experience I've had in Harlem. The staff was very warm and accommodating and took great care of me on my bday; the garnishes on the drinks, culinary books on the shelves, little touches in terms of presentation and experience were top notch...one of the managers even helped us select a beautiful bottle of wine. I've lived in the neighborhood for over 10 years and look forward to returning to Clay a lot more in the future.
Best restaurant in the area, hands down. Fantastic food, fantastic ambiance, fantastic service. Also very covid safe and conscious
Excellent food and drink in cozy, modern setting. Great date place.  I rounded up from a 4.5.

Great meal outside under a heat lamp that doubled as the spotlight to our table. Diners at all the other tables seem just as happy to be there during these trying times. Had the burger (delicious) and my friend had a pasta dish special (never finishes her meals but cleaned her plate here--😮) Recommend.

My favorite restaurant in Harlem. Everything on the menu is delicious. It's a bit pricey but you definitely get what you pay for. Highly recommend all of the seafood and any duck dishes, and the Panna cotta dessert is the best I've had.
THE best restaurant in Harlem! Super happy they’ve survived the pandemic and are still serving outstanding food in person and now delivered too. I’ll always be happy to support Clay!

Who knew??! This place is wonderful. A welcomed surprise as an out of town guest and I were on the hunt for dinner one early Sunday evening. There weren't very many guests present, which was the opposite of what I remember seeing there when the location was previously a Mexican restaurant. The vibe here is the complete opposite...quaint and charming. It's the perfect setting for a date or chill but small group dinner. If you are a solo diner the bar may be better unless you prefer to sit at a table in peace with a book and a meal...not a lot of people watching here (at the hour I was there). The food is PERFECT! I am still thinking about the Bucatini! My friends had the pork tenderloin and Garganelli, and we shared the duck fat potatoes...all were fantastic! The only qusestion mark I have is for the drinks...I ordered an Aperol Spritz, but what I received was some other spirit spritz. It was "ok" but not Aperol. The server apologized for not mentioning they did not have Aperol. The overall service and food outweighed my disappointment with my drink so I am giving Clay 5 stars! The drink wasn't that bad...I ordered a 2nd. :-)

Conned me on Valentine's Day  I am a student. I received a $100 gift card to this restaurant for Christmas. I called them the week before Valentine's Day to set something up. They said they weren't taking menu orders for Valentine's Day, but had a Valentine's Day Special they could deliver. I asked about the price, and they said $110. Now, obviously when you're doing a Valentine's Day Special, it's meant for two people, but since my finances are tight I wanted to be sure.  "$110 total," I asked, "or per person?" "No, just $110," they told me.  Well, I just got the bill. They charged $110 PER PERSON.  I very specifically asked them about this. It's negligent at best; shamelessly duplicitous at worst.  (Also, $220 for four scallops, two pieces of fish, two pieces of beef, two cookies, and some miscellaneous veggies et cetera is absurd--especially given that the food arrived cold. If you're charging this kind of price, you should at least be sending out your delivery guys with insulated containers. They just used brown paper bags.)

Yesterday we had the pleasure of eating at Clay's. It was a friend's birthday, and she invited us to go to this restaurant with her. I had two non-alcoholic drinks: Inner Flight (lemon, honey, chamomile, etc) and Fine and Mellow (with beet juice and soda). Fantastic drinks!! For our appetizers, we ordered the pork belly and the chicken liver pate with toast. Sensacional flavors and presentation. The portions were good enough to share. For my entree, I chose crab with calamarata pasta, which was phenomenal - crab really tasted like crab. My husband ordered the famous confit duck leg, and let me tell you, I never ate a duck so delicious and so crispy like this one. To wrap it up, we ordered as a dessert the yogurt pannacotta. The staff was very attentive and always checking on us. I loved that they did an outside area that was open and cozy at the same time, and I felt safe because it was only 8 tables spread out. My special shout out for one of the managers, Andrea Needell, that gave us a first class service, very nice and fun. I can't wait to go back to Clay's!

I absolutely love this restaurant. They do everything right. The staff are very professional, and have been extremely responsible during this pandemic (tables are well spaced, masks enforced, etc). More importantly, the food is exquisite. Very flavorful and creative dishes. Highly recommend this place for a special occasion or even a regular night out. PS. They give out the best dog treats too!

Rude and offstandish waitress - felt pressured and judged. Kind of made the whole experience bad from the start. The food was solid, lacked any bold flavors and portions were on the small side. Won't be coming back again.
